# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers per area.
#
# GitHub matches the LAST matching pattern for a path, so order is
# general -> specific. Owners are auto-requested for review on PRs and,
# when "Require review from Code Owners" branch protection is on, are a
# hard merge gate.
#
# NOTE: the owners below are placeholders pointing at the intended GitHub
# org/team. Replace @cooud-ui/* teams (or @pedrogbraz) with the real handles
# once the repo moves under the `cooud` org (see docs/RELEASE_GOVERNANCE.md).

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default owner for everything not matched by a more specific rule below.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*                               @pedrogbraz

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Published library packages (the public API surface — review with care).
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/packages/tokens/              @pedrogbraz
/packages/theme/               @pedrogbraz
/packages/ui/                  @pedrogbraz

# CLI is the unscoped public-npm entry point ("cooud-ui").
/packages/cli/                 @pedrogbraz

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Release & supply-chain critical surfaces — tightest review.
# CI/CD, publishing, governance, owners file, and dependency lockfile.
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
/.github/                      @pedrogbraz
/.github/workflows/            @pedrogbraz
/.github/CODEOWNERS            @pedrogbraz
/RELEASE.md                    @pedrogbraz
/docs/RELEASE_GOVERNANCE.md    @pedrogbraz
/bun.lock                      @pedrogbraz
/.npmrc                        @pedrogbraz
/package.json                  @pedrogbraz
